
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This template is for HUMAN-authored commit messages only.
# AI-authored commit messages follow ~/.claude/commit-workflow-checklist.md
# (mandatory two-line AI attribution; no decision matrices apply here).
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# UPPERCASE Conventional Commits
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Format:
#   TYPE(scope): description
#
#   [optional body]
#
#   [optional footer(s)]
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TYPE (required, UPPERCASE) — pick one:
#
#   BUILD     Changes to build system or external dependencies
#   CHORE     Routine tasks, maintenance, housekeeping
#   CI        Changes to CI configuration
#   DOCS      Documentation only
#   FEAT      New feature
#   FIX       Bug fix
#   MERGE     Merge commit
#   PERF      Performance improvement
#   REFACTOR  Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   STYLE     Formatting, whitespace (no logic change)
#   TEST      Adding or correcting tests
#   WIP       Work in progress (interim commit, will be squashed)
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SCOPE (optional) — area of the project affected:
#   e.g., (docs), (config), (build), (deps)
#
# BREAKING CHANGES — add ! before the colon:
#   e.g., FEAT(api)!: remove deprecated endpoint
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BODY (optional) — explain what and why, not how.
#   Separate from description with a blank line.
#
# FOOTER (optional) — references, breaking change details:
#   e.g., References #42         (default — links without auto-closing)
#   e.g., Closes #42             (only when this merge IS the issue's completion signal)
#   e.g., BREAKING-CHANGE: description of what broke
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
